comparison operators
>	greater than
>=	greater or equal than
<   smaller than
<=	smaller or equal than
==	equals to
!=	not equal to


logical operators

and (true if all true)
or	(true if one is true)
not	(True = False)

# this code is saved to temperature.py
temperature = 35
if temperature > 30:
	# indentation matters!!!
	print('Too hot!')

